During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer provided updates on various topics. He mentioned that Congressman Steve Scalise is making progress in his recovery and that another shooting victim, Mike Mika, has been upgraded to good condition. Spicer also discussed the signing of the VA Accountability and Whistleblower Protection Act, which aims to protect veterans from misconduct. He mentioned that the President is supportive of the Senate healthcare bill and wants to work with senators to improve it. Regarding Russia, Spicer did not comment on the President's views on the special counsel, Robert Mueller, but said that the President remains hopeful that China will apply pressure on North Korea. He also condemned the recent portrayal of violence against the President in a play and by Johnny Depp.